      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "When you believe your entire identity is lost, it is natural to feel as though there is no point in rebuilding, but consider that your true self isn't the \"perfect performance\" people liked, but the authentic person capable of feeling pain and striving for growth. This sudden loss of self-worth can feel like a complete death, yet many people discover that their humanity was never defined by their past strengths or failures, but by their capacity to learn and change moving forward. I encourage you to be incredibly gentle with yourself right now, even if you don't feel like it, and please reach out to a therapist who can help you navigate this profound sense of emptiness.",
